      "content": "In mixed-use residential districts, zoning allows for small commercial elements like a corner grocery within a residential setting, but specific rules apply. You'll need to look closely at the local code for height restrictions, parking requirements, and appropriate use designations. Regarding setbacks and encroachment, typical rules dictate minimum distances from lot lines and street right-of-ways, and exceeding these without a permit is usually a violation.",
