      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Generally, the city has a process for addressing encroachments, which usually starts with an inspection and formal notice to the property owner. For a long-standing, minor encroachment, the city might issue an order to cure the violation, requiring the owner to remedy the issue, often through removal or modification. Significant or long-term issues can lead to fines, stop-work orders, or, in extreme cases, legal action to abate the nuisance.",
